If you’ve ever found yourself mindlessly munching on a bag of chips only to feel a pang of snack regret afterward, you’re not alone. But what if we told you there’s a way to snack smart without sacrificing flavor or crunch? Say hello to homemade rye bread chips—the savory, crispy solution that’s as easy to make as it is to customize.
These golden-baked slices of heaven are perfect for charcuterie boards, as a sidekick to soups and dips, or simply for guilt-free solo snacking. Best of all? You can flavor them any way you like—from garlicky goodness to smoky spice blends. Let’s dive in.

 Why Rye?
Rye bread has a dense texture and a tangy, earthy flavor that holds up beautifully when baked into chips. It’s also typically higher in fiber and nutrients like manganese, magnesium, and phosphorus compared to white bread. That means these chips aren’t just crunchy—they’re functional fuel for your body.

 What You’ll Need
1 loaf of rye bread (store-bought or homemade)
Olive oil or melted butter
Sea salt
Optional herbs and spices (see flavor variations below)
Baking sheet
Parchment paper (optional but helpful)

 How to Make Rye Bread Chips
Step 1: Preheat & PrepPreheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Line your baking sheet with parchment paper for easy cleanup.
Step 2: Slice ThinlyUsing a sharp serrated knife, slice the rye bread into thin pieces—about ⅛-inch thick. The thinner the slice, the crispier the chip.
Step 3: Oil & SeasonPlace your slices in a large mixing bowl or lay them out flat and brush each side lightly with olive oil or melted butter. Sprinkle with sea salt and your chosen flavorings (see ideas below!).
Step 4: BakeArrange the slices in a single layer on your baking sheet. Bake for 10–15 minutes, flipping halfway through, until they’re golden brown and crisp. Keep an eye on them—thin slices can burn quickly.
Step 5: Cool & CrunchLet them cool on a wire rack. They’ll crisp up even more as they cool. Once cooled, store them in an airtight container—they’ll stay fresh for up to a week.

 Flavor Variations to Try
Here’s where the real fun begins. Try one of these flavor combos, or get creative and make your own!
1. Garlic & HerbMix garlic powder, dried oregano, thyme, and a pinch of rosemary with your oil before brushing.
2. Spicy ChipotleAdd chipotle powder, smoked paprika, and a dash of cayenne for a smoky, spicy kick.
3. Everything BagelSprinkle with “everything bagel” seasoning for a crunchy snack with a cult-favorite flavor.
4. Parmesan & Black PepperGrate a little fresh Parmesan and mix it with cracked black pepper for a bold and savory twist.
5. Dill PickleBlend dried dill, garlic powder, onion powder, and a dash of white vinegar powder for a tangy chip that pairs perfectly with creamy dips.

 What to Serve Them With
Rye bread chips are made for dipping. Try pairing them with:
Hummus or baba ghanoush
Creamy spinach dip
Smoked salmon spread
Aged cheese boards
Tomato basil soup
Or, eat them straight from the jar. No judgment here.

Final Crunch
Homemade rye bread chips are a simple yet impressive snack that delivers on flavor, texture, and nutrition. Plus, they’re a fantastic way to use up leftover bread. Once you make your first batch, you’ll wonder why you ever bought bagged chips in the first place.
So, next time your snack craving hits, skip the store and head to your kitchen. Your future self—and your taste buds—will thank you.

